data.text:
Clarissa Anderson, 65, of Scottsville, KY died Sunday, February 26, 2017 at the Medical Center at Bowling Green. The Pikeville, KY native was a retired employee of Sumitomo. She was a daughter of the late James Adams and Mazzie Phillips Adams and wife of the late Bobby C. Anderson.

She is survived by 1 daughter: Melissa Burden and husband, David, Scottville, KY;

1 son: Christopher Williams, Scottsville, KY;

1 brother: Dennis Adams, Grayson, KY;

2 grandchildren: David Ryan Burden and Bianca Burden.

Funeral services will be 11:00 a.m. Wednesday at Goad Funeral Home with Bro. Danny Patrick officiating and burial in Allen County Memorial Gardens. Visitation will be after 3:00 p.m. Tuesday at Goad Funeral Home.
